{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yakik\\Documents\\projects\\rearden","sessionId":"cc42502b-91ea-463e-bb76-8ad3ec4ad15f","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a36ece0","slug":"compressed-percolating-tower","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"I need to update all SCSS files in the Rearden web app to work with a dark theme. The project switched from a light theme to a dark theme. All hardcoded `#fff` backgrounds need to be replaced with the SCSS variable `$glassBg` (which resolves to a dark panel color). For `color: #fff` that's intentionally white text on buttons/badges, those should stay as `#fff`. For `color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, #fff)` patterns, change to `color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, $bgBase)`.\n\nRun these sed commands on Windows using Git Bash. The project is at C:\\Users\\yakik\\Documents\\projects\\rearden\\apps\\web\\src\n\nHere are the specific files and replacements needed. Run them all:\n\n```bash\ncd /c/Users/yakik/Documents/projects/rearden/apps/web/src\n\n# Background #fff -> $glassBg (panels, surfaces, inputs)\nsed -i 's/background: #fff;/background: $glassBg;/g' \\\n  pages/Landing/Landing.module.scss \\\n  pages/Search/Search.module.scss \\\n  pages/Register/Register.module.scss \\\n  pages/Resume/Resume.module.scss \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatTabBar.module.scss \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatMessageInput.module.scss \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatSidebar.module.scss \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatSearch.module.scss \\\n  components/SearchBar/SearchBar.module.scss \\\n  components/VideoUpload/VideoUpload.module.scss \\\n  components/VacancyCard/VacancyCard.module.scss \\\n  components/ChatInput/ChatInput.module.scss \\\n  components/Input/Input.module.scss \\\n  components/PostCard/PostCard.module.scss \\\n  components/Select/Select.module.scss \\\n  components/VideoPlayer/VideoPlayer.module.scss \\\n  components/Sidebar/Sidebar.module.scss\n\n# color-mix with #fff -> use $bgBase\nsed -i 's/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, #fff)/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, $bgBase)/g' \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatConversationItem.module.scss \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatConversationHeader.module.scss \\\n  components/ConversationList/ConversationList.module.scss\n\nsed -i 's/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 12%, #fff)/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 12%, $bgBase)/g' \\\n  pages/Landing/Landing.module.scss\n\nsed -i 's/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 8%, #fff)/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 8%, $bgBase)/g' \\\n  components/NotificationItem/NotificationItem.module.scss\n\n# ChatMessage bubble background\nsed -i 's/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, #fff)/color-mix(in srgb, $accentPurple 15%, $bgBase)/g' \\\n  pages/Chat/ChatMessageBubble.module.scss \\\n  components/ChatMessage/ChatMessage.module.scss\n```\n\nExecute all of these. Don't worry about the `color: #fff` cases — those are intentionally white text and should stay."},"uuid":"801a9e93-600c-4bfd-8cff-9002b8744c64","timestamp":"2026-03-23T09:48:45.361Z"}
